               <head>Treatises on farriery</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158   http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85062160">
                  <summary>A collection of treatises on farriery, together with various brief compilations of medicinal formulae for equine ailments. The first text in the manuscript, but probably the last to be copied, is in Urdu, as are parts of the third and fourth and some of the remedies elsewhere in the manuscript; the remainder is in Persian. The folios from 241 to the end are all of similar paper and most of the texts are copied by the same hand, probably during the 13th/19th century.</summary>
               </msContents>
