                        <locus from="74v" to="112v">ff 74v-112v</locus>
                        <note>
                           <p>A Persian treatise on farriery by Ḥāmid ibn ‘Alīm, in 60 chapters (bāb) of which only 58 have headings. The last two, however, are much the longest. </p>
                           <p>The chapters and their subjects, are listed on f. 74v-76r. Folios 106v-112v contain a chapter comprising medicinal formulae in verse; folios 113r-115v contain talismans.
</p>
                        </note>
                        <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22068">Farasnāmah</title>
